Fast-rising singer T.I Blaze has testified of the goodness of his senior colleague, Olamide’s recent featuring on his song. Born, Akintunde Abiodun Timileyin, featured the YBNL boss on the remix of his hit song, “Sometimes”. He said his DM hasn’t remained the same since then.   I’ve been depressed for two years – Kida Kudz     Jonathan condoles with Murray-Bruce over mother’s death     Obi Cubana congratulates Lagos hawker over varsity return   According to T.I Blaze, Baddo Sneh’s feature has gained him attraction from ladies who won’t allow his DM rest. - Advertisement - These ladies he added, are more beautiful than his mother. “I was single till OLAMIDE jumped on my song #sometimes. After that, my DM was filled with ladies that are even (more) beautiful than my mom for an ugly boy like me, different feeling,” he wrote.